The paper proposes a CNN-based framework for online multi-object tracking, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The framework utilizes single object trackers and introduces a spatial-temporal attention mechanism to handle occlusion and interaction among targets, which involves ML techniques such as feature learning and attention mechanism. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the framework involves tracking multiple objects in a dynamic environment, which involves robotics (RO) techniques. Therefore, cs.RO is also a likely sub-category.
